import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('symbol').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the average price by symbol?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Symbol')
    plt.ylabel('Average Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='date', color='blue', kde=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
